    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 137</em></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 4,000 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 18 lbs.</p>\n<p><strong>Damage</strong> 2d10 (small), 2d12 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x4; <strong>Range</strong> 50 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B and P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p>\n<p><strong>Misfire</strong> 1-2 (5 ft.); <strong>Capacity</strong> 2</p>\n<p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3>\n<p>This double-length rifle uses a pair of trunnions to mount its barrel into a swiveling mechanism fastened to the top of a lightweight, twowheeled carriage. It takes a full-round action to set up the carriage. The carriage has a hind leg, allowing the wielder to wheel the device about and immediately prop it for stability during combat.</p>\n<p>Unlike other two-handed firearms, you must fire the double hackbut while it is mounted, or else firing it imparts a -4 penalty on attack rolls and the recoil knocks you prone. A Large or larger creature can fire a double hackbut one size smaller than itself without the gun's mounting as a normal two-handed weapon and without the danger of being knocked prone, but takes the normal penalty for firing an inappropriately sized weapon.</p>\n<p><strong>This is an early firearm.</strong></p>",
